
AiLens has been installed!

Next steps:

1. Run the migration:
   $ rails db:migrate

2. Configure LLM adapters in config/credentials.yml.enc:
   openai:
     api_key: sk-...
   anthropic:
     api_key: sk-ant-...
   google:
     api_key: ...
   xai:
     api_key: ...

3. Add the Identifiable concern to your model:

   class CollectionItem < ApplicationRecord
     include AiLens::Identifiable

     identifiable_photos :photos
     identifiable_mapping(
       name: :title,
       category: :item_category,
       description: :notes
     )

     # Optional: Define a custom schema
     define_schema do |s|
       s.field :name, type: :string, required: true
       s.field :category, type: :string
       s.field :year, type: :integer
     end

     # Optional: Lifecycle callbacks
     before_identify -> (item) { item.user.has_credits? }
     on_success -> (item, job) { item.broadcast_update }
   end

4. Trigger identification:

   item = CollectionItem.find(1)
   job = item.identify!

   # With options:
   job = item.identify!(
     adapter: :anthropic,
     user_feedback: "This is a rare variant"
   )

5. Check status:

   item.identifying?  # => true/false
   item.identified?   # => true/false
   job.completed?     # => true/false

For more information, see the README at:
https://github.com/your-username/ai-lens

